# ADR-002: MCP Choices

**Date:** {{created_date}}
**Status:** Accepted

## Context

Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers extend Claude Code's toolset. Each server loads its full tool-definition set into the conversation on startup — even tools never used. This adds token overhead proportional to the number of tools.

## Decision

- **GitHub Issues / PRs** — use `gh` CLI (zero token overhead) instead of GitHub MCP (~30 tools)
- **File access** — use Claude Code built-in Read/Write/Edit/Glob/Grep instead of Filesystem MCP
- **Issue tracking** — use `gh` CLI instead of Linear MCP (~15 tools)
- **Library docs** — Context7 MCP if selected (targeted lookups, low overhead)

**Selected at init:** {{installed_mcps}}

## Consequences

- Agents use `gh issue list`, `gh pr create`, etc. for project management
- No MCP needed for file ops — built-in tools cover all needs
- Token budget stays lower; more context available for actual work
